posts.cooked: Hello World! YAGSL is a Generic Swerve Library (an actual library) aiming to simplify creating comprehensive SwerveDrives using best practices from many SwerveDrive examples. The documentation wiki is here, an example project is here, the library is here, and Javadoc are here. Features include second-order kinematics with limited state-space estimation, closed-loop PID exclusive usage, dashboards for each swerve module, support for Falcons and Neos without code changes, an actual library instead of template code, documentation including javadocs, varying encoder support, compatibility with TimedRobot, and more. The easiest way to create a SwerveDrive is through a JSON configuration directory, with a single line example provided. The library uses WPILib classes like RobotDriveBase and MotorSafety, ensures MotorSafety, and provides advanced tuning options. It also supports simulation and has low CPU utilization. There are optional dashboards for tuning and debugging. There is support for both Falcons and Neos with the same codebase, along with multiple encoder configurations. This implementation uses second-order kinematics and state-space modeling for position estimation. Simulation support exists, mainly for Neos, though Falcons require further testing. Configuration is designed to be easy for teams to use and robust enough for most SwerveDrives. I'm looking for teams willing to test YAGSL and provide feedback. Issues can also be reported through this thread. Thank you, and enjoy!
